  m_Name: Ribcage_and_Sternum.555
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Ribcage_and_Sternum.555
  partName: Ribcage and Sternum 555
  descriptionChunks:
  - The ribcage and sternum create the supportive thoracic framework surrounding
    vital organs within the canine chest cavity. Ribs extend from the thoracic vertebrae
    and connect to the sternum through cartilage, allowing flexibility necessary
    for normal breathing. This structure protects the heart, lungs,
  - and major blood vessels from external injury while supporting respiratory mechanics
    during inhalation and exhalation. Muscles attached to the ribs contribute to
    trunk stability, posture, and forelimb movement. The thoracic cage also assists
    with absorbing forces generated during locomotion.
